he operation until there is no more pastry, also using the reserved pastry in the refrigerator."},{"content":"Lay the crescents out on the prepared baking tray and cook in preheated oven for 10 to 15 minutes (180°C). They should not turn golden. Remove the gazelle horns from the oven, roll them in the remaining icing sugar and serve at room temperature."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Oriental cuisine is very rich in almond- and honey-based pastries to accompany the traditional mint tea. Oriental cakes come in shapes inspired by nature or fauna, such as these gazelle horns."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","1h","25 pieces"]}